Tags:
  - 1031
By: Sri Sankarâchârya
---
I do not ask of Thee, O Mother! riches, good fortune, or salvation; I seek
no happiness, no knowledge. This is my only prayer to Thee： that, as the
breath of life forsakes me, still may I chant Thy Holy Name.
